				<li id="16575667" class="cmnt-root" data="16" data-d="1648524411000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><a class="comment-username" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&u=128301" rel="nofollow"  target="_blank" style="color: #;">agnacore</a></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579054/Aspects-of-the-Crucible:-Horns" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">28 Mar 2022 23:26</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16575667" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">As others have said, no seal boosts the Primordial Crucible incantations; however, if you were to do a Crucible Knight build, you would most likely want the Clawmark Seal. The two Crucible Knight weapons, Ordovis&apos; Greatsword and Siluria&apos;s Tree, both use STR and FTH, and the Clawmark Seal just so happens to scale its offensive incantations with the same stats. Combine this with the armor&apos;s passive bonus (I think it&apos;s ~4% per piece, not positive as I only read it here) and you should be doing good damage. Have fun!</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16575667" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16575667" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">3</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>16</p><i class="add">+1</i></s